tafsir[17]{c,v,t}:
  86,1,"Allah took an oath by the sky and He took an oath by the star that knocks at night."
  86,2,"O Messenger! What will tell you the status of this great star?!"
  86,3,"It is the star that pierces the sky with its glowing light."
  86,4,"There is no soul except that Allah has assigned to it an angel to record its deeds for the reckoning on the day of judgment."
  86,6,"Allah created him from a spurting liquid that is split into the womb."
  86,7,"This liquid emerges from between the spinal column of a man and the bones of the chest."
  86,15,"Those who deny what their messenger brought to them plot and scheme to reject and refute his call."
  86,16,"I too plot and scheme to make the religion victorious and to disprove falsehood."
  87,2,"The One Who created man in due proportion and balanced his stature."
  87,4,"The One Who brought out from the earth what your animals graze on."
  87,5,"The He made it into dry blackish straw after it had been green and fresh."
  87,7,"Except for what Allah wishes you to forget for some reason. He (may He be glorified) knows what is made public and what is hidden. Nothing of that is hidden from Him."
  87,8,"I will make it easy for you to do actions that please Allah and enter you into Paradise."
  87,9,"So give counsel to people with the Qur’ān that I reveal to you and remind them as long as the reminder is heard."
  87,12,"The one who will enter the great Fire of the afterlife to suffer and bear its heat forever."
  87,14,"The one who purified himself from idolatry and sins has attained the objective."
  87,15,"Who remembered his Lord by the various forms of remembrance that He ordained. Who discharged the prayer in the required manner."